  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The intestinal microflora imbalance has been associated with obesity and type 2 diabetes. The
      researchers' study aimed to investigate the effect of saxagliptin on gut microbiota in
      patients with newly diagnosed type 2 diabetes.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
